      "content": "Our investigation analyzes the thermal-induced structural transformations of various metals subjected to high-pressure environments. By implementing in-depth kinetic and thermodynamic simulations, our study quantitatively evaluates the metallurgical properties alterations under extreme thermal conditions. Our empirical results reveal a consistent weakening in material strength correlated with temperature elevation, highlighting critical insights for industrial applications involving high-temperature, high-pressure metallurgical processes. The findings advance the existing knowledge of deformation mechanisms in metallic materials, thus contributing valuable theoretical foundations in the domain of materials science.",
      "source": "target",
